Gran Fondo: Texas TMCO
description: In the Gran Fondo format made popular in recent years, this first year event will add its own twist. A fundraising ride for the Texas Medical Center Orchestra and the National MS Society, the \"timed\" component of the route will be an extended distance of up to 78 miles, allowing for racers to race, recreational riders to ride and all to compare their results. Awards will be awarded by category and then by age.
course: The route begins with flat well paved roads and leads to the rolling beauty of northern Waller County and Grimes County and the 6-7% hills surrounding Whitehall before ending on the flats again.
notes: After a 5 mile neutral zone, riders will roll over the timing mats and begin the race.
directions: 35 miles northwest of I10/ I610 interchange off Hwy 290.  Exit Hwy 290 at Hegar Road and travel north 5 miles.  Gate to property is on the right.  Follow signs to parking area.

title: The Rocket Race @ Sansom Park
description: Cross country mountain bike race as a fundraiser for Fort Worth Mountain Bikers\' Assocaition.. No refunds but we do offer the option to sign up online and pay day of. Prepaid online riders will receive a significant discount. Discounts also for active FWMBA and DORBA club members. This is meant as a \"fun\" race so results are unofficial and will not be included in any formal rankings or series points with any racing organization or sanctioning body. No racing license will be required.
course: Mass start for all categories and classifications. All riders will ride the same course with the only difference being number of laps.
notes: Make up date of 12/17 in case of inclement weather.
directions: Marion Sansom Park of Robert\'s Cutoff Road in Fort Worth, TX.
